DataType.Description: This DataType is an Enumeration that represents the NMT reset commands for POWERLINK

uax:Description.uax:Text: readback value for the POWERLINK Object NMT_ResetCmd_U8

Field.Name: NMTResetNode
Field.Description: start application initialisation

Field.Name: NMTResetCommunication
Field.Description: start communication initialisation

Field.Name: NMTResetConfiguration
Field.Description: activate device configuration

Field.Name: NMTSwReset
Field.Description: start basic node initialisation

Field.Name: NMTInvalidService
Field.Description: readback value for the POWERLINK Object NMT_ResetCmd_U8

DataType.Description: This DataType is an enumeration that represents the NMT State

uax:Description.uax:Text: first state after power-on of the POWERLINK Device
set manufacturer-specific and standardised device profile area to their power-on values
set communication profile area (except ERR_History_ADOM) to their power-on values
a non-permanent state which allows a starting device to recognize the current network state
the POWERLINK network operates in reduced cycle
the POWERLINK network operates in isochronous operation, but the device is still in a configuration state
the device configuration is completed and the device is ready to switch over to NMT_XS_OPERATIONAL
normal operating state of a POWERLINK Device
the device is largely passive, NMT_CS_STOPPED shall be used for controlled shutdown of a selected CN while the system is still running
Legacy Ethernet communication according to IEEE 802.3, no POWERLINK specific network traffic control

Field.Name: NMT_GS_INITIALISING
Field.Description: first state after power-on of the POWERLINK Device

Field.Name: NMT_GS_RESET_APPLICATION
Field.Description: set manufacturer-specific and standardised device profile area to their power-on values

Field.Name: NMT_GS_RESET_COMMUNICATION
Field.Description: set communication profile area (except ERR_History_ADOM) to their power-on values

Field.Name: NMT_GS_RESET_CONFIGURATION
Field.Description: generate the active device configuration

Field.Name: NMT_XS_NOT_ACTIVE
Field.Description: a non-permanent state which allows a starting device to recognize the current network state

Field.Name: NMT_XS_PRE_OPERATIONAL_1
Field.Description: the POWERLINK network operates in reduced cycle

Field.Name: NMT_XS_PRE_OPERATIONAL_2
Field.Description: the POWERLINK network operates in isochronous operation, but the device is still in a configuration state

Field.Name: NMT_XS_READY_TO_OPERATE
Field.Description: the device configuration is completed and the device is ready to switch over to NMT_XS_OPERATIONAL

Field.Name: NMT_XS_OPERATIONAL
Field.Description: normal operating state of a POWERLINK Device

Field.Name: NMT_CS_STOPPED
Field.Description: the device is largely passive, NMT_CS_STOPPED shall be used for controlled shutdown of a selected CN while the system is still running

Field.Name: NMT_XS_BASIC_ETHERNET
Field.Description: Legacy Ethernet communication according to IEEE 802.3, no POWERLINK specific network traffic control

DataType.Description: Represents the values of the POWERLINK ErrorRegister

Field.Name: Generic_error
Field.Description: This bit shall be set if any error is present. Additionally to this bit, the following bits may be used to signal more detailed error information.

Field.Name: Reserved
Field.Description: always 0

Field.Name: Const
Field.Description: Read access only, the value is not changing

Field.Name: Read
Field.Description: Read access

Field.Name: Write
Field.Description: Write access

Field.Name: Input
Field.Description: Represents process input data, object can be used in PDO mapping

Field.Name: Output
Field.Description: Represents process output data, object can be used in PDO mapping

Field.Name: Store
Field.Description: Can be stored to non-volatile memory

Field.Name: ValidOnReset
Field.Description: Only valid after reset

Field.Name: DefaultMapping
Field.Description: Variable is included in default mapping

Field.Name: RPDO
Field.Description: Variable may be mapped into receive PDO

Field.Name: TPDO
Field.Description: Variable may be mapped into transmit PDO

DataType.Description: Represents the entries of the POWERLINK Object ERR_History_ADOM (Object 1003h, SubIndex 1..254)

Field.Name: entryType
Field.Description: Entry type as defined in the Powerlink specification EPSG DS 301

Field.Name: errorCode
Field.Description: Error code as defined in the Powerlink specification EPSG DS 301

Field.Name: timeStamp
Field.Description: SoC Nettime from the cycle when the error/event was detected

Field.Name: additionalInformation
Field.Description: This field contains device profile or vendor specific additional error information

DataType.Description: Structure DataType PowerlinkIpAddressDataType to represent POWERLINK Objects of the POWERLINK data type IP_ADDRESS

Field.Name: b1
Field.Description: 1st byte of the IP-Address, e.g. 192 for the Address 192.168.100.1

Field.Name: b2
Field.Description: 2nd byte of the IP-Address, e.g. 168 for the Address 192.168.100.1

Field.Name: b3
Field.Description: 3rd byte of the IP-Address, e.g. 100 for the Address 192.168.100.1

Field.Name: b4
Field.Description: 4th byte of the IP-Address, e.g. 1 for the Address 192.168.100.1

DataType.Description: Structure DataType PowerlinkPDOMappingEntryDataType to represent the entries of POWERLINK Objects like PDO_RxCommParam_00h_REC

Field.Name: length
Field.Description: Index of the object to be mapped

Field.Name: offset
Field.Description: Sub-Index of the object to be mapped

Field.Name: reserved
Field.Description: for alignment purpose

Field.Name: subIndex
Field.Description: Offset related to start of PDO payload (Bit count)

Field.Name: index
Field.Description: Length of the mapped object (Bit count)
